(1) All Alerts
-----------------

      <div class="alert alert-primary">A simple dark alert—check it out!</div>
      <div class="alert alert-secondary">A simple dark alert—check it out!</div>
      <div class="alert alert-success">A simple dark alert—check it out!</div>
      <div class="alert alert-danger">A simple dark alert—check it out!</div>
      <div class="alert alert-warning">A simple dark alert—check it out!</div>
      <div class="alert alert-info">A simple dark alert—check it out!</div>
      <div class="alert alert-light">A simple dark alert—check it out!</div>
      <div class="alert alert-dark">A simple dark alert—check it out!</div>
      
      
(2) Link Color
---------------

      <div class="alert alert-primary">
        A simple dark <a href="#" class="alert-link">alert—check</a> it out!
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-secondary">
        A simple dark <a href="#" class="alert-link">alert—check</a> it out!
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-success">
        A simple dark <a href="#" class="alert-link">alert—check</a> it out!
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-danger">
        A simple dark <a href="#" class="alert-link">alert—check</a> it out!
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-warning">
        A simple dark <a href="#" class="alert-link">alert—check</a> it out!
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-info">
        A simple dark <a href="#" class="alert-link">alert—check</a> it out!
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-light">
        A simple dark <a href="#" class="alert-link">alert—check</a> it out!
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-dark">
        A simple dark <a href="#" class="alert-link">alert—check</a> it out!
      </div>
      
      
(3) Alert With Additional Content
-----------------------------------

	<div class="alert alert-success" role="alert">
	  <h4 class="alert-heading">Well done!</h4>
	  <p>Aww yeah, you successfully read this important alert message. This example text is going to run a bit longer so that you can see how spacing within an alert works with this kind of content.</p>
	  <hr>
	  <p class="mb-0">Whenever you need to, be sure to use margin utilities to keep things nice and tidy.</p>
	</div>
	
	
(4) Dismissing Alert
---------------------

      <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade show" role="alert">
        <h4 class="alert-heading">Well done!</h4>
        <p>
          Aww yeah, you successfully read this important alert message. This
        </p>
        <button class="close" data-dismiss="alert">
          &times;
        </button>
      </div>
